   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "53684fa5-7b0a-4ee9-87c4-596dfffaa45a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Mutable Sequence Types"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "77898377-eac5-4354-947b-d2e2697545b1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Mutating Objects\n",
    "\n",
    "names = ['Eric', 'John'] \n",
    "names -> Eric John 0xFF255\n",
    "\n",
    "names = names + ['Michael']\n",
    "names -> Eric John Michael 0xAA235 (different memory address)\n",
    "\n",
    "This is not mutation!\n",
    "Mutating an object means changing object state without creating a new one.\n",
    "\n",
    "names = ['Eric', 'John']\n",
    "names -> Eric John 0xFF255\n",
    "names.append('Michael')\n",
    "names -> Eric John Michael 0xFF255"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "abb412a3-cf9a-42ef-b5b4-a19daec495df",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Mutating Using []\n",
    "\n",
    "s[i] = x (element at index i replaced with x)\n",
    "s[i:j] = s2 (slice is replaced by contents of iterable s2)\n",
    "del s[i] (removes element at index i)\n",
    "del s[i:j] (removes entire slice)\n",
    "\n",
    "We can even assign to extended slices\n",
    "s[i:j:k] = s2\n",
    "\n",
    "Come back to mutating using slicing later."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "id": "ec14be32-e43e-4073-be92-22d4cee571e1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Some other methods supported by mutable sequence types such as lists\n",
    "\n",
    "s.clear() (removes all items from s)\n",
    "s.append(x) (appends x to the end of s)\n",
    "s.insert(i, x) (inserts x at index i)\n",
    "s.extend(iterable) (appends contents of iterable to the end of s)\n",
    "s.pop(i) (removes and returns element at index i)\n",
    "s.remove(x) (removes the first occurence of x in s)\n",
    "s.reverse() (does an in-place reversal of elements of s)\n",
    "s.copy() (returns a shallow copy)\n",
    "\n",
    "and more...."
   ]
  },
